W H Y T H E C O M B I N A T I O N W O R K S
Layer 1 measures directional transition in momentum structure. Layer 2 measures position within the

compression-release cycle. A signal fires only when both simultaneously confirm: the market is at a grid-
defined release point AND is undergoing an I Ching expansion transition.

The two systems are mathematically independent — they measure different phenomena using different
frameworks. Their simultaneous agreement filters out the majority of false positives that either system
would generate alone.

Mathematical Structure

The I Ching operates on a base-8 system: 8 trigrams, 64 hexagrams (8x8). The proprietary grid operates
on a 36-position structure (6x6). Together: 64 + 36 = 100.
The I Ching's base-2 architecture can encode states 0 through 7. State 8 — the 9th state in the mod-9
system — has no trigram equivalent. The grid contains nodes at State 8. This means the grid encodes
something the I Ching structurally cannot represent. The grid is mathematically a completion of the I
Ching into the dimension it cannot itself reach.
These structural relationships were not designed into the grid. They were discovered after the fact. The
grid arrived as a complete sequence of 36 numbers. The mathematical properties were found through
analysis, not construction.

What the Signal Detects

After testing 22 assets across 7 asset classes, a clear pattern emerged. The signal works on markets
that exhibit endogenous compression dynamics — where price pressure accumulates from within the
market's own participant structure and discharges internally.
It does not work on markets driven primarily by external catalysts — weather events, central bank
decisions, harvest cycles, geopolitical shocks.
